// ccsesh config — examples for the Enter action.
//
// ccsesh reads STRICT JSON from ~/.config/ccsesh/config.json (or wherever
// $XDG_CONFIG_HOME points). To try an example below, copy it into
// config.json and remove the leading "// " comments. JSON itself does not
// support comments — this .example.jsonc file uses them for readability.
//
// Placeholders in "enter.command":
//   {sid}  — session id (auto shell-escaped)
//   {cwd}  — original project directory (auto shell-escaped)
//
// When no config.json exists (or .enter.command is empty), Enter runs the
// default: cd into {cwd} and `claude --resume {sid}` in the current tab.
//
// Note on GUI terminals (Ghostty, iTerm2, etc.): their AppleScript /
// "new tab with command" APIs exec the configured command via a stripped
// login shell (no rc files, minimal PATH). Homebrew/nvm/asdf installs of
// `claude` typically are NOT on that minimal PATH. The cleanest fix is to
// delegate to a tiny wrapper script that resolves `claude`'s absolute path
// in a normal shell before invoking the AppleScript. See the `examples/`
// directory in the ccsesh repo for ready-made wrappers.

// ── WezTerm: resume in a new tab ──────────────────────────────────────
// Ready-made wrapper in examples/wezterm-new-tab handles the PATH issue.
// { "enter": { "command": "~/.local/bin/wezterm-new-tab {sid} {cwd}" } }

// ── iTerm2: resume in a new tab ───────────────────────────────────────
// Ready-made wrapper in examples/iterm2-new-tab types the command into
// the tab's shell (so rc files load and PATH is intact).
// { "enter": { "command": "~/.local/bin/iterm2-new-tab {sid} {cwd}" } }

// ── Ghostty 1.3+: resume in a new tab ─────────────────────────────────
// Ready-made wrapper in examples/ghostty-new-tab handles the PATH issue.
// { "enter": { "command": "~/.local/bin/ghostty-new-tab {sid} {cwd}" } }

// ── tmux: resume in a new window ──────────────────────────────────────
// { "enter": { "command": "tmux new-window -c {cwd} -- claude --resume {sid}" } }

// ── Delegate to your own script ───────────────────────────────────────
// { "enter": { "command": "~/bin/ccsesh-enter {sid} {cwd}" } }
